SliceTrueTalbe = [False] * log_data.shape[0]
for feature in log_data.keys():
    
    # TODO: Q125th
    Q1 = np.percentile(log_data[feature], 25)
    
    # TODO: Q375th
    Q3 = np.percentile(log_data[feature], 75)
    
    # TODO: 1.5
    step = 1.5 * (Q3 - Q1)
    
    # 
    print("Data points considered outliers for the feature '{}':".format(feature))
    display(log_data[~((log_data[feature] >= Q1 - step) & (log_data[feature] <= Q3 + step))])
    
    tempTable = ~((log_data[feature] >= Q1 - step) & (log_data[feature] <= Q3 + step))
    SliceTrueTalbe = SliceTrueTalbe | tempTable

from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# 
cluster_data = pd.read_csv("cluster.csv")
y = cluster_data['Region']
X = cluster_data.drop(['Region'], axis = 1)

# 
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=24)

clf = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=24)
clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
score_with_cluster = clf.score(X_test, y_test)

# cluster
X_train = X_train.copy()
X_train.drop(['cluster'], axis=1, inplace=True)
X_test = X_test.copy()
X_test.drop(['cluster'], axis=1, inplace=True)
clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
score_no_cluster = clf.score(X_test, y_test)

print("cluster: %.4f"%score_no_cluster)
print("cluster: %.4f"%score_with_cluster)
